------------------------------------------------------------
--------------            Structure           --------------
------------------------------------------------------------
- DMWAW* and libmwaw_libwpd* : files which come directly of libwpD/src/lib
- TMWAW* and libmwaw_tools* : some basic Tools ( mostly generic )
- IMWAW* and libmwaw_internal* : internal core part of libmwaw (ie. classes used by many parser )
- MWAW* : specific classes ( MWAW document )
- CW* : parser of ClarisWorks and AppleWorks documents
- MW* : parser of MacWrite documents
- WP* : parser of WriterPlus documents
------------------------------------------------------------
--------------            Exported           --------------
------------------------------------------------------------

## new interface	
- libmwaw.hxx
- IMWAWDocument.hxx

## wrapper to the old interface
- libmwaw.h
- IMWAWDocument.h

------------------------------------------------------------
--------------   files DMWAW and libmwaw_libwpd  --------------
------------------------------------------------------------
These files are the files which come directly of libwpd/src/lib

In order to avoid conflict problems, all WPX classes are renamed DMWAW while other classes, ..  are defined in namespace libmwaw_libwpd.

## libs_libwpd (from libwpd_internal) : 
   - introduction of new attributes DMWAW_ALL_CAPS_BIT/DMWAW_EMBOSS_BIT/DMWAW_ENGRAVE_BIT bits
   - comments some WP5/WP6 fonts

## DMWAWContentListener by
   - introduction of a new field m_paragraphLineSpacingUnit
   - gestion of  DMWAW_ALL_CAPS_BIT/DMWAW_EMBOSS_BIT/DMWAW_ENGRAVE_BIT bits
   - virtualize _appendParagraphProperties in order to add border flags
   - change in WPXContentListener::justificationChange

## WPXListener :
   - m_pageList is no longer a reference on a std::list<WPXPageSpan>

## WPXOLEStream :
   - correct the function fullName
   - add a function allEntries to retrieve all the leaves names

   - add a function to retrieve dir and file name from olename
   - add a function to flatten a name

------------------------------------------------------------
--------------   files TMWAW and libmwaw_tools  --------------
------------------------------------------------------------

These files defined basic tools which must be used by the parsers :
## libmwaw_tools.hxx
	define MWAW_DEBUG_MSG, shared_ptr, Vec2, Vec3 and Box2

## TMWAWInputStream.hxx
	internal wrapper of WPXInputStream (with function to read Ole, ...)

## generic tools

- TMWAWDebug.hxx : class to store parsed data in an intermediate file
- TMWAWFont.hxx : read and convert in unicode Apple© char fonts
- TMWAWPrint.hxx : read the mac printer information
- TMWAWOleParser.hxx : read some classic ole structure
- TMWAWPropertyHandler.hxx : some classes which keep a list of tag and WPXPropertyList,
	store/unstore then in order to be reread by writerperfect 

## tool for graphics:
- TMWAWPict.hxx : generic pict
- TMWAWPictBasic.hxx : simple pict (line, rectangle, oval, ..)
- TMWAWPictBitmap.hxx : a class to keep basic bitmap(ie. a 2D array of some type) and transforms them in PBM, PPM
- TMWAWPictData.hxx : basic class to manage a pict form by a chunck of classic data ( included MWAWPicMac)
- TMWAWPictMac.hxx : check macintosh Pict1.0, Pict2.0, 2.1 and convert Pict1.0 in Pict2

------------------------------------------------------------
-------------- files IMWAW and libmwaw_internal --------------
------------------------------------------------------------

Internal classes which can depend on WPX internal and tools

These files defined basic structures which must be used by the parsers :

## libmwaw_internal.hxx
	define a small function used to print tabulation and
	include libmwaw_tools.hxx

## IMWAWContentListener.hxx
## IMWAWHeader.hxx
## IMWAWSubDocument.hxx
	Files to parse document inspired of libwpd/WP*

## IMWAWEntry.hxx
	store an file entry as begin/end offset with the name of the entry
	such an entry is used by all msworks file (excepted Mac v1, v2, v3)

## IMWAWParser.hxx
	a basic parser
## IMWAWTextParser.hxx
	a basic parser which can help to store the text data
	and read a FDPP or FDPC entry, such entry exists in all files
	(excepted Mac v1, v2, v3)

------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------   CW/MW/WP -------------------
------------------------------------------------------------
Generic classes : 

MWAWContentListener.cxx 
MWAWStruct.cxx 
MWAWTools.cxx

Specific files which depends on the type of file which is converted


############# Mac

CWParser : parser of ClarisWorks/AppleWorks document
-   CWGraph : class which reads the graphics and zone dispositions ...
-   CWDatabase/CWSpreadSheet : class which reads the database/spreadsheet structure ( uncomplete)
-   CWTable : class which reads the table structures
-   CWText : class which reads the text and its structures

MWParser : parser of MacWrite document : v2.2 v4.5
WPParser : parser of WriterPlus document